865
00:44:51,800 --> 00:44:54,480
"But he mustn't know it's from us," says Ricki.

866
00:44:54,480 --> 00:44:56,600
"Yes, you're right, but we can send the message  

867
00:44:56,600 --> 00:45:00,400
from my dad's computer and use a 
false user name," replies Trish.

868
00:45:00,400 --> 00:45:02,720
"He's going to think the message is from Pat!"

869
00:45:02,720 --> 00:45:04,480
"How?" asks Stacy.

870
00:45:04,480 --> 00:45:06,320
"We don't have Pat's password."

871
00:45:06,320 --> 00:45:07,800
"We can trick Eric.

872
00:45:07,800 --> 00:45:12,600
We can write to him with a new user name 
and tell him that it's Pat's new user name.

873
00:45:12,600 --> 00:45:16,960
We can say that he has a new user name 
now because the old one isn't safe."

874
00:45:16,960 --> 00:45:19,720
"What are we going to write 
in the message?" asks Tony.

875
00:45:19,720 --> 00:45:22,640
"It's too late to write the 
message now," replies Trish.

876
00:45:22,640 --> 00:45:24,720
"We have to think about it carefully.

877
00:45:24,720 --> 00:45:27,880
Let's meet tomorrow afternoon at 
my house to prepare the message.

878
00:45:27,880 --> 00:45:30,560
Tony, can you give Stacy and me a ride home?"

879
00:45:30,560 --> 00:45:33,120
"Sure, I have my mom's car tonight.

880
00:45:33,120 --> 00:45:34,640
It's parked outside.

881
00:45:34,640 --> 00:45:36,400
Come on, girls, let's go.

882
00:45:36,400 --> 00:45:38,600
Ricki, see you tomorrow."

883
00:45:38,600 --> 00:45:39,840
"Okay, guys, bye.

884
00:45:39,840 --> 00:45:43,760
See you," replies Ricki sleepily.

885
00:45:43,760 --> 00:45:48,240
On the way home in Tony's car, Tony and 
the girls are talking about the party.

886
00:45:48,240 --> 00:45:51,560
Tony comes to a red light and 
puts his foot on the brake.

887
00:45:51,560 --> 00:45:52,840
But something is wrong.

888
00:45:52,840 --> 00:45:54,440
The car doesn't stop.

889
00:45:54,440 --> 00:45:58,040
Tony pushes and pushes on the 
brake pedal, but nothing happens.

890
00:45:58,040 --> 00:45:58,760
"Tony!

891
00:45:58,760 --> 00:45:59,440
Tony!

892
00:45:59,440 --> 00:46:00,560
What are you doing?

893
00:46:00,560 --> 00:46:03,400
Stop the car!" shouts Stacy.

894
00:46:03,400 --> 00:46:04,840
"I can't!" cries Tony.

895
00:46:04,840 --> 00:46:06,480
"The brakes aren't working!"

896
00:46:06,480 --> 00:46:09,200
Another car is coming towards them very fast.

897
00:46:09,200 --> 00:46:12,040
Tony turns the wheel hard to avoid the other car.

898
00:46:12,040 --> 00:46:15,440
The girls see the black post of the 
traffic lights in front of them.

899
00:46:15,440 --> 00:46:19,640
Stacy screams as the car smashes 
violently into the traffic lights.

900
00:46:19,640 --> 00:46:21,400
They all fall from their seats.

901
00:46:21,400 --> 00:46:22,640
A few minutes pass.

902
00:46:22,640 --> 00:46:24,800
They sit immobilized with shock.

903
00:46:24,800 --> 00:46:28,600
Trish recovers first and turns 
to look at her two friends.

904
00:46:28,600 --> 00:46:30,640
Tony is slumped over the steering wheel.

905
00:46:30,640 --> 00:46:31,560
He isn't moving.

906
00:46:31,560 --> 00:46:32,720
His eyes are shut.

907
00:46:32,720 --> 00:46:34,080
He looks very pale.

908
00:46:34,080 --> 00:46:36,040
"Tony!" cries Trish.

909
00:46:36,040 --> 00:46:36,560
"Oh my God!

910
00:46:36,560 --> 00:46:36,960
Tony!

