965
00:49:17,920 --> 00:49:19,960
"That's it!" shouts Trish.

966
00:49:19,960 --> 00:49:23,880
"We've got them!" She prints the 
message and puts it in her school hag.

967
00:49:23,880 --> 00:49:28,200
"Tomorrow afternoon we can go and see Mr 
Stockton and tell him everything we know."

968
00:49:28,200 --> 00:49:33,680
"But we still don't know exactly what Eric 
and Pat did, or who helped them," says Ricki.

969
00:49:33,680 --> 00:49:37,920
"You're right, but Mr Stockton 
can investigate that," says Stacy.

970
00:49:37,920 --> 00:49:40,640
"We don't want any more trouble."

971
00:49:40,640 --> 00:49:43,240
The next morning Tony and 
Ricki are in the computer  

972
00:49:43,240 --> 00:49:46,400
room at school working on a math’s problem.

973
00:49:46,400 --> 00:49:50,520
Suddenly Pat, Kyle and Eric come into the room.

974
00:49:50,520 --> 00:49:55,240
They close the door and Kyle puts a chair 
in front of it so no one can come in.

975
00:49:55,240 --> 00:49:56,880
Tony is nervous.

976
00:49:56,880 --> 00:49:59,560
"What do you want, Pat?" he asks.

977
00:49:59,560 --> 00:50:02,840
"Don't move, Caruso!" says Eric sharply.

978
00:50:02,840 --> 00:50:03,800
"Sit down.

979
00:50:03,800 --> 00:50:04,720
Now!"

980
00:50:04,720 --> 00:50:08,120
"You think you're really 
smart, you two, don't you?

981
00:50:08,120 --> 00:50:10,360
Well, we're on to you," says Pat.

982
00:50:10,360 --> 00:50:14,480
"I don't know what you're talking 
about," replies Ricki, defiantly.

983
00:50:14,480 --> 00:50:21,040
"Now, Anderson, that's not very honest for a 
good little boy scout like you," sneers Eric.

984
00:50:21,040 --> 00:50:23,640
"Yeah, a boy that's always 
top of the class and sucks  

985
00:50:23,640 --> 00:50:27,640
up to Coach Bergman to get on the team!" adds Pat.

986
00:50:27,640 --> 00:50:31,800
Eric shows them a print-out of their 
e-mail with the false user name.

987
00:50:31,800 --> 00:50:35,000
"Kyle was at my house yesterday when I got this.

988
00:50:35,000 --> 00:50:37,680
He went to play billiards with Pat.

989
00:50:37,680 --> 00:50:41,760
He asked Pat about his new user 
name, but Pat didn't know anything."

990
00:50:41,760 --> 00:50:43,600
Tony and Ricki say nothing.

991
00:50:43,600 --> 00:50:45,480
They feel scared.

992
00:50:45,480 --> 00:50:49,800
"I suppose now you want to go blab 
to old Stockton, eh, Anderson?

993
00:50:49,800 --> 00:50:51,720
Well, we're going to teach you a lesson.

994
00:50:51,720 --> 00:50:54,400
You have to understand we mean business."

995
00:50:54,400 --> 00:50:58,200
Ricki stands up but Eric steps 
forward and pushes him to the ground.

996
00:50:58,200 --> 00:50:59,760
He's very angry.

997
00:50:59,760 --> 00:51:02,880
Ricki tries to get up but Eric pushes him again.

998
00:51:02,880 --> 00:51:05,920
He pulls Ricki's hair and 
lifts his arm to punch him.

999
00:51:05,920 --> 00:51:08,320
"Get off the basketball team, Anderson.

1000
00:51:08,320 --> 00:51:10,360
I'm going to fix you!"

1001
00:51:10,360 --> 00:51:14,200
Tony tries to catch Eric's arm, 
but Kyle and Pat hold him back.

1002
00:51:14,200 --> 00:51:15,960
"Eric, don't!" he shouts.

1003
00:51:15,960 --> 00:51:17,000
"That's not the way.

1004
00:51:17,000 --> 00:51:18,320
Don't make any more trouble."

1005
00:51:18,320 --> 00:51:26,560
"Shut up, Caruso, you're next!" shouts 
Eric.
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 

1006
00:51:30,440 --> 00:51:32,200
CHAPTER ELEVEN

1007
00:51:32,200 --> 00:51:34,400
Return to the Team

1008
00:51:34,400 --> 00:51:38,360
Suddenly they hear voices in the corridor outside.

1009
00:51:38,360 --> 00:51:42,240
Ricki sees Stacy's face at 
the glass panel in the door.

1010
00:51:42,240 --> 00:51:45,320
Someone tries to open the 
door from the other side.

1011
00:51:45,320 --> 00:51:48,160
Kyle shouts to Pat to help him keep it shut.

1012
00:51:48,160 --> 00:51:49,760
Eric is too angry to notice.

1013
00:51:49,760 --> 00:51:51,120
He hits Ricki on the head.

1014
00:51:51,120 --> 00:51:52,320
Ricki is on the floor.

1015
00:51:52,320 --> 00:51:54,040
He can't get up because of his leg.

1016
00:51:54,040 --> 00:51:56,600
Then he sees his crutches 
next to the computer table.

1017
00:51:56,600 --> 00:51:58,360
If he can reach one of them...

1018
00:51:58,360 --> 00:52:01,080
He grabs Eric's leg and pulls him down.

1019
00:52:01,080 --> 00:52:07,560
Eric falls and, at that moment Ricki grabs 
the crutch and pins him down with it.

1020
00:52:07,560 --> 00:52:12,720
The door opens with a crash and Mr Stockton and 
some of the senior boys burst into the room.

1021
00:52:12,720 --> 00:52:14,520
"That's enough, boys!" he shouts.

1022
00:52:14,520 --> 00:52:18,480
"Caplin, Martin, Jones - go 
to my office immediately.

1023
00:52:18,480 --> 00:52:20,400
You're in serious trouble.

1024
00:52:20,400 --> 00:52:22,560
The police are coming for you."

1025
00:52:22,560 --> 00:52:24,360
Eric is furious.

1026
00:52:24,360 --> 00:52:26,800
As the seniors lead him and the others away,  

1027
00:52:26,800 --> 00:52:30,480
he shouts at Ricki and Tony, 
"I'm going to finish you!

1028
00:52:30,480 --> 00:52:36,160
I'm going to break your other leg, 
Anderson - and yours too, Caruso!"

1029
00:52:36,160 --> 00:52:41,520
Later the four friends are in the lunch room at 
school when Mr Stockton walks over to the table.

1030
00:52:41,520 --> 00:52:44,640
He smiles at the four students.

1031
00:52:44,640 --> 00:52:48,200
"Kyle, Pat and Eric are not going 
to be in school for a while.

1032
00:52:48,200 --> 00:52:53,440
The police are investigating their part in Ricki's 
accident and the problems with Tony's mom's car.

1033
00:52:53,440 --> 00:52:56,880
Kyle and Pat aren't going to 
play basketball this year.

1034
00:52:56,880 --> 00:53:00,200
Coach says he doesn't want 
trouble-makers on the team."

1035
00:53:00,200 --> 00:53:05,480
He turns to Ricki, "I see you don't have 
your crutches any more, Ricki," he adds.

1036
00:53:05,480 --> 00:53:08,120
"When are you going to start 
basketball practice again?"

1037
00:53:08,120 --> 00:53:10,640
"Well, the doctor says my leg is much better.

1038
00:53:10,640 --> 00:53:14,480
I can start playing again 
next month," replies Ricki.

1039
00:53:14,480 --> 00:53:21,080
"That's good, but take it easy - you don't 
want to hurt your leg again," says Mr Stockton.

1040
00:53:21,080 --> 00:53:25,080
"Now, there's a newspaper reporter 
in my office who wants to talk you.

1041
00:53:25,080 --> 00:53:29,720
He wants to do a story in the local 
newspaper about Eric and your accidents.

1042
00:53:29,720 --> 00:53:31,720
Come to my office in thirty minutes.

1043
00:53:31,720 --> 00:53:35,040
Stacy, Trish - you two girls, too."

1044
00:53:35,040 --> 00:53:38,840
Later in the afternoon, Ricki 
and Tony are in the locker room.

1045
00:53:38,840 --> 00:53:42,920
Tony is getting ready for practice when 
Anthony comes in and talks to them.

1046
00:53:42,920 --> 00:53:45,960
"Kyle Martin and Pat Jones are off the team.

1047
00:53:45,960 --> 00:53:47,960
Coach says I'm on the team!

1048
00:53:47,960 --> 00:53:50,440
I'm going to play in the game on Friday night!"

1049
00:53:50,440 --> 00:53:54,960
"That's great, Anthony - you're a good 
player, you deserve it," says Ricki, smiling.

1050
00:53:54,960 --> 00:54:00,520
"I hope your leg gets better and you can start 
playing again soon, Ricki," replies Anthony.

1051
00:54:00,520 --> 00:54:04,640
"We're going to be a fantastic team this year!"

1052
00:54:04,640 --> 00:54:06,800
They walk out onto the basketball court.

1053
00:54:06,800 --> 00:54:09,040
Ricki sits down to watch the practice session.

1054
00:54:09,040 --> 00:54:13,400
He thinks, "Now all the trouble 
is finished, I just want to play  

1055
00:54:13,400 --> 00:54:23,960
basketball!"
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 

1056
00:54:23,960 --> 00:54:25,200
CHAPTER TWELVE

1057
00:54:25,200 --> 00:54:27,480
Ricki's Long Shot

1058
00:54:27,480 --> 00:54:30,960
Four weeks later the 
basketball championship starts.

1059
00:54:30,960 --> 00:54:35,840
The boys from Howard High are in the gym 
practicing for their first game on Saturday.

1060
00:54:35,840 --> 00:54:37,240
Ricki is back!

1061
00:54:37,240 --> 00:54:39,760
It's his first practice since the accident.

1062
00:54:39,760 --> 00:54:42,920
He wants Coach Bergman to 
choose him to play on Saturday.

1063
00:54:42,920 --> 00:54:46,520
He tries to run fast but his leg hurts a bit.

1064
00:54:46,520 --> 00:54:49,640
"Take it easy, Anderson!" shouts Coach Bergman.

1065
00:54:49,640 --> 00:54:51,000
"Don't force your leg.

1066
00:54:51,000 --> 00:54:53,520
We need you for the game on Saturday night!"

1067
00:54:53,520 --> 00:54:55,080
Ricki is pleased.

1068
00:54:55,080 --> 00:54:57,120
He is going to play in the game!

1069
00:54:57,120 --> 00:54:59,000
He works hard during practice.

1070
00:54:59,000 --> 00:55:01,320
He shoots well, he plays intelligently in  

1071
00:55:01,320 --> 00:55:04,680
the practice game, he plays 
well with the other players.

1072
00:55:04,680 --> 00:55:07,720
After practice, he and Tony walk to the showers.

1073
00:55:07,720 --> 00:55:10,880
"You played great tonight, Ricki," says Tony.

1074
00:55:10,880 --> 00:55:15,240
"If you play like that on Saturday, 
Redwood High doesn't have a chance!"

1075
00:55:15,240 --> 00:55:18,840
Coach Bergman comes into the 
locker room to talk to Ricki.

1076
00:55:18,840 --> 00:55:23,560
"Anderson," he says, "I think you're 
ready to play in a real match.

1077
00:55:23,560 --> 00:55:25,320
I want you there on Saturday.

1078
00:55:25,320 --> 00:55:27,680
You and Caruso are a great duo!"

1079
00:55:27,680 --> 00:55:31,320
"Thanks, Coach, that's fantastic!" replies Ricki.

1080
00:55:31,320 --> 00:55:35,000
"Oh, and Ricki, I'm sorry for 
what happened to you and Tony.

1081
00:55:35,000 --> 00:55:39,080
Caplin and the others were really out of 
control but they're going to be punished.

1082
00:55:39,080 --> 00:55:42,640
I hope now they understand 
their behavior was very wrong.

1083
00:55:42,640 --> 00:55:47,200
You can't become a good basketball player by 
threatening other players or hurting them.

1084
00:55:47,200 --> 00:55:51,960
You and Tony are not only better players 
but you're better sportsmen than they are."

1085
00:55:51,960 --> 00:55:53,680
"Thanks, Coach," says Tony.

1086
00:55:53,680 --> 00:55:55,440
"We're going to work hard.

1087
00:55:55,440 --> 00:56:01,600
We appreciate that you chose us to be on the 
team, even if we're juniors," says Tony sincerely.

1088
00:56:01,600 --> 00:56:02,720
"Okay, boys.

1089
00:56:02,720 --> 00:56:16,960
Show me I was right - win the match against 
Redwood High on Saturday!" laughs Coach Bergman.

1090
00:56:16,960 --> 00:56:19,360
It's Saturday night and the arena is full.

1091
00:56:19,360 --> 00:56:21,760
There are a lot of people watching the game.

1092
00:56:21,760 --> 00:56:26,320
The band is playing loud music and the 
cheerleaders are dancing with their pompoms.

1093
00:56:26,320 --> 00:56:28,400
The two teams run onto the court.

1094
00:56:28,400 --> 00:56:33,240
They practice shooting and throwing the ball.

1095
00:56:33,240 --> 00:56:35,960
Then the buzzer sounds and the game begins.

1096
00:56:35,960 --> 00:56:38,400
Coach Bergman calls his players into a group.

1097
00:56:38,400 --> 00:56:40,560
"Well, guys, this is our first game of the year.

1098
00:56:40,560 --> 00:56:41,960
Redwood has a good team.

1099
00:56:41,960 --> 00:56:43,600
It's going to be a tough match.

1100
00:56:43,600 --> 00:56:45,800
Do your best."

1101
00:56:45,800 --> 00:56:47,120
All the players nod.

1102
00:56:47,120 --> 00:56:51,440
They join hands in a circle 
and shout, "Go, go, go!

1103
00:56:51,440 --> 00:56:53,520
Fly high, Howard Hawks!!!"

1104
00:56:53,520 --> 00:56:55,320
The crowd jumps to its feet.

1105
00:56:55,320 --> 00:56:59,360
Everyone is clapping and 
shouting, "Go Hawks!" Some  

1106
00:56:59,360 --> 00:57:02,120
people wave flags with pictures of hawks on them.

1107
00:57:02,120 --> 00:57:04,680
The team feels the energy of the crowd.

1108
00:57:04,680 --> 00:57:06,440
They are excited and tense.

1109
00:57:06,440 --> 00:57:08,160
They want to win.

1110
00:57:08,160 --> 00:57:12,200
At half time, the score is 46-40 for Redwood.

1111
00:57:12,200 --> 00:57:14,120
Both teams are playing very well.

1112
00:57:14,120 --> 00:57:18,080
At the end of the second half 
the score is even at 63-63.

1113
00:57:18,080 --> 00:57:20,800
There are only 15 seconds left.

1114
00:57:20,800 --> 00:57:23,040
The crowd is wild with excitement.

1115
00:57:23,040 --> 00:57:25,240
Coach Bergman calls a timeout.

1116
00:57:25,240 --> 00:57:26,160
"Okay, boys.

1117
00:57:26,160 --> 00:57:27,440
We only have one more shot.

1118
00:57:27,440 --> 00:57:29,400
Anderson, do you want to take the shot?"

1119
00:57:29,400 --> 00:57:31,480
"You bet, Coach," Ricki replies.

1120
00:57:31,480 --> 00:57:32,000
"Okay, then.

1121
00:57:32,000 --> 00:57:34,440
Do all of you remember the set-up?"

1122
00:57:34,440 --> 00:57:39,160
"Yes, Coach," the players say.

1123
00:57:39,160 --> 00:57:40,280
The buzzer sounds.

1124
00:57:40,280 --> 00:57:42,720
They go back onto the court.

1125
00:57:42,720 --> 00:57:45,400
Tony passes the ball to 
Anthony who throws it to Don.

1126
00:57:45,400 --> 00:57:48,200
Don dodges two Redwood 
players and passes to Ricki.

1127
00:57:48,200 --> 00:57:51,787
Ricki jumps, takes aim quickly 
and throws the ball at the basket.

1128
00:57:51,787 --> 00:57:53,320
Is the shot too short?

1129
00:57:53,320 --> 00:57:55,440
He's still a long way from the basket.

1130
00:57:55,440 --> 00:57:56,600
It doesn't go in.

1131
00:57:56,600 --> 00:58:00,080
Ricki's heart sinks but the 
referee is blowing his whistle.

1132
00:58:00,080 --> 00:58:01,920
Ricki has two free shots!

1133
00:58:01,920 --> 00:58:04,160
He goes to the free-throw line.

1134
00:58:04,160 --> 00:58:05,600
He takes aim and shoots.

1135
00:58:05,600 --> 00:58:08,480
The hall hits the basket but it doesn't go in.

1136
00:58:08,480 --> 00:58:09,800
He misses the shot!

1137
00:58:09,800 --> 00:58:12,800
"I have to make this second 
shot," he thinks to himself.

1138
00:58:12,800 --> 00:58:15,160
"It's our last chance!"

1139
00:58:15,160 --> 00:58:17,520
This is the longest shot of his life.

1140
00:58:17,520 --> 00:58:21,720
He takes a deep breath, fixes his 
eye on the basket, and shoots.

1141
00:58:21,720 --> 00:58:24,520
The hall goes around the edge of the basket twice.

1142
00:58:24,520 --> 00:58:30,160
He thinks, "Go in, please go in!" 
Then, the ball drops - it's in!

1143
00:58:30,160 --> 00:58:31,280
Ricki scores!

1144
00:58:31,280 --> 00:58:33,080
The crowd goes crazy!

1145
00:58:33,080 --> 00:58:35,220
The Hawks win the game by one point!

1146
00:58:35,220 --> 00:58:40,880
The players carry Ricki on their shoulders 
around the arena and the crowd shouts and cheers.

1147
00:58:40,880 --> 00:58:44,800
He sees his parents standing, 
waving to him - they are very proud.

1148
00:58:44,800 --> 00:58:48,440
He sees Stacy jumping and 
cheering and Trish next to her.

1149
00:58:48,440 --> 00:58:52,000
He knows that this is the 
happiest moment of his life.

1150
00:58:52,000 --> 00:58:55,160
After all the difficulties 
he had before this game,  

1151
00:58:55,160 --> 00:59:22,800
now he knows it was worth it - 
the day he played the long shot.

